  "prompt": "Is that true- people pass Physical test of SSC SI by giving some amount to field officer who inspect the activity?",
  "response": "No, it is not true that candidates can pass the **Physical Efficiency Test (PET)** or **Physical Standard Test (PST)** for the **SSC Sub-Inspector (SI)** exam by paying a bribe to field officers. The **Staff Selection Commission (SSC)** conducts these tests with strict monitoring and transparency to ensure fairness and integrity in the recruitment process.\n\nSuch claims are often baseless rumors or attempts to spread misinformation. Any form of malpractice or bribery is illegal and\u917f\u9020\u4e25does not guarantee success. On the contrary, it can lead to disqualification or legal consequences for both the candidate and the involved officials.\n\nCandidates are advised to prepare diligently for the physical tests and follow the official guidelines provided by SSC. If there are any concerns about irregularities during the process, they should report the matter to the appropriate authorities. Always rely on hard work and honesty to succeed in competitive exams like SSC SI.",
